  - [ ] Iframe state management documentation
  - [ ] Navigation and interaction documentation

## Implementation Steps

- [ ] **Story 4.1: Implement Persistent User Settings for Layout**
  - [ ] Define UserSetting Prisma model with theme and menuPosition
  - [ ] Update User model with relation to UserSetting
  - [ ] Create migration and apply to database
  - [ ] Add logic to auto-create UserSetting records
  - [ ] Implement backend API for user settings
  - [ ] Enhance session data with user preferences
  - [ ] Create UI controls in User Settings page
  - [ ] Add dynamic header adaptation based on preferences
  - [ ] Implement dynamic dashboard layout based on preferences
  - [ ] Create theme application and toggle functionality
  - Success criteria: Users can personalize layout and theme with persistence
  - Dependencies: Epic 1 (User Schema), Epic 2 (User Profile)

- [ ] **Story 4.2: Implement Core Iframe State Management**
  - [ ] Create IframeProvider React Context
  - [ ] Implement useIframeManager custom hook
  - [ ] Add iframe rendering logic
  - [ ] Implement CSS visibility control
  - [ ] Add iframe sandbox attributes for security
  - [ ] Create mechanisms for tracking loaded status
  - [ ] Implement state preservation verification
  - [ ] Add support for initial URL loading
  - Success criteria: Robust iframe state management with visibility control
  - Dependencies: Story 3.9

- [ ] **Story 4.3: Implement Desktop "Top Menu" Navigation Experience**
  - [ ] Create conditional rendering for AppBar central area
  - [ ] Implement normal state display with opacity/underline indicators
  - [ ] Add hover-to-expand interaction
  - [ ] Create expanded view interaction handling
  - [ ] Implement responsive adaptation for tablets
  - [ ] Ensure proper layout and scrolling
  - Success criteria: Rich, intuitive "Top Menu" experience with visual indicators
  - Dependencies: Stories 3.8, 4.1, 4.2

- [ ] **Story 4.4: Implement Desktop "Side Menu" Navigation Experience**
  - [ ] Create conditional rendering based on preferences
  - [ ] Implement side panel structure with full-height layout
  - [ ] Add collapsible behavior for desktop/tablet
  - [ ] Create URL/Group interaction with indicators
  - [ ] Ensure proper integration with IframeManager
  - [ ] Add smooth animations and transitions
  - Success criteria: Rich, organized "Side Menu" experience with visual indicators
  - Dependencies: Stories 4.1, 4.2

- [ ] **Story 4.5: Implement Click and Long-Press for URLs**
  - [ ] Create single-click behavior for all menus
  - [ ] Implement long-press detection with visual feedback
  - [ ] Add unload action for long-press
  - [ ] Create UI for unloaded active URLs
  - [ ] Implement cancellation of long-press
  - [ ] Ensure proper integration with IframeManager
  - Success criteria: Intuitive URL interactions with visual feedback
  - Dependencies: Story 4.2

- [ ] **Story 4.6: Ensure Advanced Features Work in Mobile Drawer**
  - [ ] Implement visual states for mobile drawer URL items
  - [ ] Add click interaction in mobile context
  - [ ] Create long-press interaction with haptic feedback
  - [ ] Ensure mobile usability and touch optimization
  - [ ] Maintain consistency with desktop experiences
  - Success criteria: Consistent, rich mobile experience for URL interactions
  - Dependencies: Stories 4.2, 4.5

## Affected Components

- User settings schema and APIs
- React contexts and custom hooks
- Dashboard layout and navigation components
- Iframe management system
- Interaction handlers (click, long-press)
- Mobile-specific components

## Dependencies

- Epic 1 (User Schema, Authentication)
- Epic 2 (User Profile Management)
- Epic 3 (Basic Iframe Display, Header)
- Material UI v6
- React Context API

## Technical Considerations

- Iframe state preservation requires careful implementation
- Long-press detection needs debounce and animation synchronization
- Visual indicators must update instantly on state changes
- Theme application must support system preference detection
- Mobile touch interactions need proper event handling

